(RollingStone.com) -- Paul McCartney has rescheduled the U.S. tour dates he had originally scheduled to begin in mid-June for October.

His "Out There" tour will now resume in Albany, New York on July 5.

The former Beatle is still recuperating from the virus that forced him to postpone several dates in Japan and South Korea. See the rescheduled dates, as well as McCartney's July and August dates, below.

